{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17588845","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17588845"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T09:11:51+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T09:11:51+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15175"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15175","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15175"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.91,0,0.09,0,0]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7866"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64581"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"7866","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/7866"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15175"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50015"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4928"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"8127"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19173"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19176"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21310"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64581","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/64581"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EMalignant tumours of the stomach can arise from different cell types within the gastric wall.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most common malignant gastric tumour?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Adenocarcinoma","Gastric lymphoma","Gastrointestinal stromal tumour","Neuroendocrine tumour","Squamous cell carcinoma"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAdenocarcinomas\u003C/strong\u003E account for approximately 95% of all malignant gastric tumours. \u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGastrointestinal stromal tumours\u003C/strong\u003E arise from interstitial cells of Cajal and represent less than 1% of gastric tumours. \u003Cstrong\u003ESquamous cell carcinoma\u003C/strong\u003E is extremely rare in the stomach and is more commonly found in the oesophagus. \u003Cstrong\u003EGastric lymphoma\u003C/strong\u003E accounts for about 4% of gastric malignancies. \u003Cstrong\u003ENeuroendocrine tumours\u003C/strong\u003E are rare in the stomach, comprising less than 1% of gastric neoplasms.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGastric adenocarcinoma typically develops through a sequence of pathological changes beginning with chronic gastritis, progressing through atrophic gastritis, intestinal metaplasia, and dysplasia before developing into invasive cancer. Major risk factors include infection with \u003Cem\u003EHelicobacter pylori\u003C/em\u003E, smoking, high salt diet, and family history.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Adenocarcinoma accounts for approximately 95% of all malignant gastric tumours.","Gastric adenocarcinoma commonly develops through a sequence from chronic gastritis to atrophy to metaplasia to dysplasia.","Risk factors for gastric adenocarcinoma include Helicobacter pylori infection, smoking, and high salt diet."],"references":["Ajani JA, Lee J, Sano T, Janjigian YY, Fan D, Song S. Gastric adenocarcinoma. Nat Rev Dis Primers. 2017 Jun 1;3:17036. doi: 10.1038/nrdp.2017.36. PMID: 28569272.","Smyth EC, Nilsson M, Grabsch HI, van Grieken NC, Lordick F. Gastric cancer. Lancet. 2020 Aug 29;396(10251):635-648. doi: 10.1016/S0140-6736(20)31288-5. PMID: 32861308.","Mukkamalla SKR, Recio-Boiles A, Babiker HM. Gastric Cancer. [Updated 2023 Jul 4]. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan-. Available from: https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/books/NBK459142/","Yamada, T., Alpers, D. H., Kalloo, A. N., Kaplowitz, N., Owyang, C., \u0026 Powell, D. W. (Eds.). (2011). Textbook of gastroenterology. John Wiley \u0026 Sons","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50015"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15175"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"50015","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/50015"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-24T10:44:41+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-24T10:45:11+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"7866"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"64581"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4928","links":{"self":"h